&gt; I have to admit that I thought I had seen the worst &#39;paranormal&#39;
show on television already. I was wrong. Door to the Dead has exceeded
my worst expectations.
&gt;  
&gt; Generally, I respect John Oliver&#39;s work as a medium. While I have no
personal experience with him, in the past he has looked and acted more
genuine than not, the rolling of the eyes put aside for the moment.
&gt;  
&gt; I do take exception to the characterization of the talking box as an
Edison device. I have documented the history of Edison, ITC and
EVP  elsewhere. This is however the smallest concern I have with this
show.
&gt;  
&gt; Prior to wathcing I had just had a conversation with a respected
colleague on the West coast regarding interesting phenomena he and
others are constantly observing in sites with phenomena similar to
that on Door to the Dead. None of those measurements were made by this
team. The use of thermal in this situation is not indicated as well.
&gt;  
&gt; The real concern is that no attempt was made to help this family in
a broader context. The skeptic did and said nothing skeptical as far
as I could tell. Key questions were not asked (at least on-camera)
that would reveal the psycho-dynamics of this family. We know fairly
well at this time that PK phenomena is often centered on a focal
person who can exhibit specific characteristics. That the team seems
unaware of this is quite disturbing to a person like myself.
&gt;  
&gt; A real research opportunity was lost in this case, as was an
opportunity to educate the public on the right way to approach such
situations. Continually sending the messages that phenomena is based
on &#39;demons&#39; and &#39;spirits&#39; exclusively does nothing to further the
position of serious investigators, which is perhaps most troubling of all.
